---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Getting Started" description="Get started with coverit — AI-powered test quality for your codebase.">
  <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-text">Getting Started</h1>

  <!-- What is coverit? -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">What is coverit?</h2>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    AI made writing code trivially easy. But shipping fast without knowing if your code is
    actually solid? That's just accumulating risk. Coverage numbers don't tell you the truth. coverit does.
  </p>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    coverit is an AI-powered test quality platform. It scans your codebase across 5 quality
    dimensions (mapped to ISO 25010), identifies real gaps, generates tests to fill them, and
    tracks your quality score over time. Everything revolves around
    <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">coverit.json</code> &mdash;
    a persistent, git-tracked quality manifest that serves as the single source of truth.
  </p>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The entire system is built on four commands:
    <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">scan</code>,
    <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">cover</code>,
    <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">fix</code>, and
    <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">status</code>.
    AI does the heavy lifting &mdash; exploring your code with real tool access, understanding your
    architecture, and writing tests that actually pass.
  </p>

  <!-- Prerequisites -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">Prerequisites</h2>
  <ul class="ml-6 list-disc mb-4">
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">
      <strong>Node.js 18+</strong> &mdash; required for running coverit
    </li>
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">
      <strong>Claude Code</strong> (recommended) &mdash; coverit works best inside Claude Code,
      where it runs as an MCP server and the AI can use tools directly. You can also use it
      standalone with any supported <a href="/docs/providers" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover underline">AI provider</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <!-- Installation -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">Installation</h2>

  <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-3 text-text">1. Claude Code (Plugin)</h3>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Install the plugin for MCP tools, slash commands, and CLAUDE.md instructions:
  </p>
  <pre class="bg-bg-code text-[#f5f0e8] font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>/plugin marketplace add devness-com/coverit
/plugin install coverit@coverit</code></pre>

  <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-3 text-text">2. Other AI Tools (MCP)</h3>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    For Cursor, Windsurf, VS Code, Gemini CLI, Zed, Cline, Codex, Goose, and more &mdash;
    run the setup wizard. It scans for AI tools on your machine and configures the MCP server interactively:
  </p>
  <pre class="bg-bg-code text-[#f5f0e8] font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>npx @devness/coverit</code></pre>

  <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-3 text-text">3. CLI (Standalone)</h3>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Use directly via <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">npx</code> in
    any project &mdash; no MCP or plugin required:
  </p>
  <pre class="bg-bg-code text-[#f5f0e8] font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>npx @devness/coverit scan      # Scan your codebase
npx @devness/coverit cover     # Generate tests for gaps
npx @devness/coverit fix       # Fix failing tests via AI
npx @devness/coverit status    # Show quality dashboard</code></pre>

  <!-- Your first scan -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">Your first scan</h2>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Navigate to your project root and run the scan command. AI will explore your codebase,
    discover modules, map existing tests, classify complexity, and identify user journeys
    and API contracts:
  </p>
  <pre class="bg-bg-code text-[#f5f0e8] font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>npx @devness/coverit scan</code></pre>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    This creates <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">coverit.json</code> in
    your project root with a complete quality manifest including your baseline score.
  </p>

  <!-- View your score -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">View your score</h2>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Check your quality dashboard at any time. This command is instant &mdash; it reads directly
    from <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">coverit.json</code> with
    no AI calls:
  </p>
  <pre class="bg-bg-code text-[#f5f0e8] font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>npx @devness/coverit status</code></pre>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The dashboard shows your overall score (0&ndash;100), broken down across quality dimensions:
    Functionality, Security, Stability, Conformance, and Regression.
  </p>

  <!-- Generate tests -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">Generate tests</h2>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Have AI generate tests to fill the gaps identified by your scan:
  </p>
  <pre class="bg-bg-code text-[#f5f0e8] font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>npx @devness/coverit cover</code></pre>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The AI reads the gaps in <code class="bg-bg-warm px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-sm">coverit.json</code>,
    writes test files for each module, runs them, fixes any failures, and updates your quality score.
    You'll see a before/after comparison when it finishes.
  </p>

  <!-- Fix failures -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">Fix failures</h2>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    If you have existing tests that are failing, let the AI fix them:
  </p>
  <pre class="bg-bg-code text-[#f5f0e8] font-mono text-sm p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>npx @devness/coverit fix</code></pre>
  <p class="font-body text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
    This runs your existing test suite, sends any failures to the AI for fixing, rescans the
    codebase, and updates your score. It's the fastest way to go from red to green.
  </p>

  <!-- Next steps -->
  <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-4 border-b border-border pb-2 text-text">Next steps</h2>
  <ul class="ml-6 list-disc mb-4">
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">
      <a href="/docs/commands" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover underline">Command Reference</a> &mdash;
      Full documentation for all commands and their options
    </li>
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">
      <a href="/docs/config" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover underline">Configuration</a> &mdash;
      Customize coverit with a config file
    </li>
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">
      <a href="/docs/providers" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover underline">AI Providers</a> &mdash;
      Choose between Claude, Gemini, Codex, OpenAI, Anthropic API, or Ollama
    </li>
    <li class="mb-2 font-body text-text leading-relaxed">
      <a href="/docs/mcp" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover underline">MCP Setup</a> &mdash;
      Use coverit as an MCP server inside Claude Code and other AI tools
    </li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
